fields.title: No cheaters in 15 Premier games
fields.content:
My group of five have encountered no obvious cheaters in the last 15 games (friday-monday) on EU servers.

Our average elo has been 17-18k. The only annoying part has been playing against a super large range of players. Encountered some 3k+ faceit players and some very new players. I guess distributing ranks in nob-cheater environment will take a while.

fields.title: ALGS 2024 Split 1 Playoffs: Lower bracket
fields.content:
Following an unsuccessful performance in the group stage, NAVI Apex Legends team has to fight for survival in the lower bracket of the ALGS: 2024 Split 1 Playoffs.

The losers' first-round matches begin today at 19:00 CET. Participants will battle six times: three on the World's Edge map and the rest on Storm Point. To advance to the next round, the team must place among the tournament's top ten based on the match results.

If NAVI players accomplish this task, they will move on to the lower bracket second round, which takes place the night after the first (starts on Sunday at 04:00 CET). If it doesn't go their way, the team will leave the tournament.

Support our guys during the livestream!

fields.title: Dust 2 returns to the CS competitive map pool
fields.content:
This evening, Valve has released a major update to CS2, with further improvements and optimizations to the game. The changes have also affected competitive Counter-Strike, as Dust 2 has returned to the map pool, replacing Overpass.

For Born to Win, these changes are positive. In the last three months, our team has only played twice on Overpass, and we scored a win against BetBoom at the PGL Major Copenhagen 2024 Europe RMR A (13 : 4).

In 2022, Dust 2 was one of the best NAVI maps: In eighteen matches, our team was defeated only three times and finished the year with 83.3% of victories on this map.

It should be noted that the ESL Pro League S19 will be played on the previous update, so we can expect a few farewell Overpass games from NAVI!

fields.title: NAVI Youth - Champions of United21 Season 12: Division 2
fields.content:
The United21 Season 12: Division 2 tournament is over. Our CS2 team NAVI Youth became the champion of the competition and won $2,000. In addition to the cash prize, Born to Win also received an invitation to the first division of United21 Season 15.

In the tournament's Grand Final, NAVI Youth easily defeated 777 Esports with a score of 2 : 0, who they had lost to in the group stage.
It should be noted that this was the only defeat that our junior roster had to accept in the championship. First Born to Win defeated Sashi Academy (2 : 1) in the deciding match of Group D, and then quickly moved to the top of the playoff bracket by defeating Metizport X (2 : 0), Preasy Rising (2 : 0), and SINNERS Academy (2 : 0).

Congratulations to the team on their first major victory! NAVI Youth's next games will take place in the 49th season of the ESEA League Main Division. Check out the schedule on our website.

fields.title: NAVI returns to Apex Legends
fields.content:
NAVI esports club is returning to Apex Legends. Orgless and Hungry, formerly known as Vexed Gaming, will now perform under the club's banner. The team is made up of experienced players who have been performing professionally for quite a while - MaTaFe, Tyler, and KIND4.

Orgless and Hungry have consistently shown excellent results in the EMEA regional competition: they became silver medalists of the last ALGS 2023 Split Pro League, and they are holding on to the second place in the tournament table this season.

The first NAVI matches in Apex Legends will take place on March 10. This day will determine 20 teams to play in the finals of the Split 2 Pro League. Don't miss the broadcast, and support our team!

fields.title: Join the CS2 Challenge in NAVI Discord
fields.content:
We continue to develop our Discord community and want to determine the best aimer among fans. The top three players will receive NAVI Jersey 2023.

#NAVINATION Target Challenge will take place on the aim_botz map in CS2. To take part, join the NAVI Discord server. Add the map to your Steam Workshop Favorites, launch it, and select "Mode #1 100 kills 90". Click on start and then everything is simple: the faster you destroy 100 bots, the higher your place in the ranking.

Don't forget about a few important things: a screenshot of the result must be shared on a dedicated server channel, and only M4A4, M4A1-S, and AK-47 can be used.

The ten best players of the first stage will advance to the finals, where prizes from NAVI will be awarded. The first stage will last 14 days, so there is not much time, good luck!
